{"name": "link-pty", "metadata": {"name": "link-pty", "version": "0.6.0", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": "https://github.com/ricepastem/link_pty", "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["websockets", "requests", "psutil"], "summary": "A package to manage pseudo terminals via WebSocket", "upload_time": 1734533089}, "documentation": ["# link_pty\r\n\r\nlink_pty is a Python package that allows you to manage pseudo terminals via WebSocket. It supports creating, managing, and interacting with terminals remotely through a WebSocket connection.\r\n\r\n## Installation\r\n\r\nTo install the package:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\npip install link_pty\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Usage\r\nAfter installing, you can run the terminal manager with:\r\n\r\n```bash\r\nlink-pty --base-url \"your_base_url_here\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nIf no base URL is provided, it defaults to linkpty.codesocean.top:43143.\r\n\r\n"], "modules": [{"name": "link_pty", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "link_pty.run_terminal_manager", "xref": {"fqname": "link_pty.terminal_manager.run_terminal_manager", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "link_pty.terminal_manager", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "link_pty.terminal_manager.run_terminal_manager", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "link_pty.terminal_manager.TerminalManager", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "link_pty.terminal_manager.TerminalManager.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "base_url", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "link_pty.terminal_manager.TerminalManager.is_ws_connected", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "docume